column1: Between 1 July 2019 and 30 June 2020, will an armed group from Pakistan engage in a campaign that systematically kills 1,000 or more civilians in Pakistan?

column6: New government is way better in controlling murders than what it was few years/months ago. It may not be able to make much progress but definitely they are moving in correct direction.

Tensions are running very high in the region and the category "armed group from Pakistan" is very broad. While 1,000 kills is a high number, basically requiring a more-or-less "systematic" attempt, I think the situation is volatile enough that such an effort could actually gain traction. 30% chance.
Very unlikely but going from 0 to 1% given Kashmir and potential fallout
There would have to be a secular uprising. The other side though? Maybe.
So PM Kahn was greeted with street protests upon his return from D.C. Pushing up to 6% for now.
